- "Short commute" refers to travel time less than 15 minutes; 
- "Study diligently" means more than 10 hours of study per week; 
- "No failures" means zero past class failures; 
- "At least one educated or professionally successful parent" refers to having a parent with an education level of 3 or higher or a parent working as a teacher or in health; 
- "Attending the school for the right reasons" means the student chose the school for the course or other reasons, not for home or reputation.

- Poor grades are typically considered as scores below a certain threshold, in this case, less than 5; 
- Low parental support is commonly defined as a level of support that hinders a student's ability to excel academically; 
- A history of class failures indicates previous instances where a student has not met the requirements to pass a class or course; 
- Moderate alcohol consumption is often defined within the range of 3 to 4 on a scale of 1 to 5, where 1 is abstinent and 5 is frequent consumption; 
- Frequent absences are typically considered as more than 5 instances of absence in a given period.
